                  <summary>Authorization issued by Diogenes and Chaeremon for the payment of 32 artabae to Andronicus. Practically complete. (Grenfell &amp; Hunt)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Text is on one side only, 7 lines written with the fibers.  All four margins intact.</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Museum of Archaeology and Anthropology collection</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>11.1 x 9.4cm. There is a large vertical tear on the left, with some loss of writing.  There is also a hole in the bottom line.  The left tear appears to be a crease that has become separated, as there seems to be a similar crease mark on the right side of the papyrus.</support>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
               </physDesc>
